<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BFA97FC07F9D4" blockId="16.[136,1452,914,2057]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BFA97FEA1FABC" bold="true" box="[189,342,1346,1372]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FE84FA96FDD2FABC" authorityName="Pursh" authorityYear="1814" box="[370,549,1346,1373]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FE84FA96FDD2FABC" box="[370,549,1346,1373]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FC2DFA97FB46FABC" box="[987,1201,1346,1372]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FC2DFA97FBA3FABC" box="[987,1108,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region by the characteristic small, unwinged, rounded, isodiametric fruit which are black when mature, within the native range of the species some plants may have large fruit but these have yet to be recorded outside the Americas. Some fruit, particularly on herbarium specimens, may appear narrowly winged at the apex. These may resemble fruit of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FB16FA7AFA92FA28" authorityName="von Linne" authorityYear="1753" box="[1248,1381,1454,1481]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FB16FA7AFA92FA28" box="[1248,1381,1454,1481]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which they can usually be distinguished by the fruit which are more or less isodiametric, however some herbarium material of these two species cannot reliably be determined. The shape of the rosette leaves, with an abrupt transition from the petiole to the broadly almost circular blade is also a useful character.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97C03CFDFF91FF82FF4BF9EBFC31F7E8" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BF9EBFB60F8EC" blockId="16.[136,1452,914,2057]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BF9EBFEAEF9B8" bold="true" box="[189,345,1598,1624]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Non-native to the region. Within the region, this species has been reported from the Waikato River, where it was first collected in 1900 (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FD99F9B7FCC5F99C" author="Webb, C. J. &amp; Sykes, W. R. &amp; Garnock-Jones, P. J." box="[623,818,1634,1661]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" refId="ref37555" refString="Webb, C. J., Sykes, W. R. &amp; Garnock-Jones, P. J. (1988) Flora of New Zealand. Vol. IV. Naturalised Pteridophytes, Gymnosperms, Dicotyledons. Botany Division D. S. I. R., Christchurch, New Zealand." type="book" year="1988">
Webb 
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FD4FF9B6FD1CF99C" box="[697,747,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">et al</emphasis>
. 1988
</bibRefCitation>
) and the Chatham Islands (de Lange 
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FB21F9B6FAFEF99C" box="[1239,1289,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">et al</emphasis>
. 1988). It was thought to be endemic to the Americas, occurring from northern 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FC83F953FC3EF940" box="[885,969,1670,1696]" name="Canada" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Canada</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FBF2F953FB8EF940" box="[1028,1145,1670,1696]" name="Greenland" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Greenland</collectingCountry>
south throughout much of North America, through Central America to 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FD89F97FFD4BF924" box="[639,700,1706,1732]" name="Chile" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Chile</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FD05F97FFC95F924" box="[755,866,1706,1732]" name="Argentina" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FC84F97FFBDBF924" author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[882,1068,1706,1732]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" pagination="364 - 369" refId="ref33036" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2009) Nomenclatural notes on Callitriche (Callitrichaceae) in North America. Novon 19: 364 - 369. https: // doi. org / 10.3417 / 2008030" type="journal article" year="2009">Lansdown 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FBCEF97FFA50F924" author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Christenhusz, M. J. M." box="[1080,1447,1706,1732]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" refId="ref33342" refString="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Christenhusz, M. J. M. (2011) Callitriche. In: Davidse, G., Sousa, M. S. &amp; Knapp, S. (eds.) Flora Mesoamericana. Vol. 1. Missouri Botanical Garden Press, Mexico City, St. Louis, and London." type="book" year="2011">Lansdown &amp; Christenhusz 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FF7EF91BFE1EF908" author="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Hassemer, G." box="[136,489,1742,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" pagination="85 - 118" refId="ref33574" refString="Lansdown, R. V. &amp; Hassemer, G. (2021) The genus Callitriche in south America. Phytotaxa 501 (1): 85 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 501.1.3" type="journal article" year="2021">Lansdown and Hassemer 2021</bibRefCitation>
). See maps on pages 176 and 
<quantity id="1822C293FF91FF82FCB2F91BFC7BF908" box="[836,908,1742,1768]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5212" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" unit="in" value="178.0">178 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FC63F91AFBCEF909" author="Fassett, N. C." box="[917,1081,1742,1769]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" pagination="209 - 222" refId="ref31146" refString="Fassett, N. C. (1951) Callitriche in the New World. Rhodora 53: 137 - 155, 161 - 182, 185 - 194, 209 - 222, plates 1167 - 1175." type="journal article" year="1951">Fassett (1951)</bibRefCitation>
. However, it occurs on 
<collectingRegion id="1D1EA194FF91FF82FABFF91BFA5CF908" box="[1353,1451,1742,1768]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
Island (WTU357850) suggesting that it may also be native to the eastern seaboard of 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FBB3F927FB64F8EC" box="[1093,1171,1778,1804]" name="Russia" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Russia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BF8C3FC22F899" blockId="16.[136,1452,914,2057]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BF8C3FE3AF8D0" bold="true" box="[189,461,1814,1840]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Habitats and Ecology:</emphasis>
—This species will occur in most water body 
<typeStatus id="0061D1D4FF91FF82FC11F8C2FBD2F8D1" box="[999,1061,1815,1841]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">types</typeStatus>
, including fast-flowing rivers and streams, backwaters and ditches, swamps, 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FD99F8EFFD12F8B4" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[623,741,1850,1876]" class="Sphagnopsida" family="Sphagnaceae" genus="Sphagnum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sphagnales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FD99F8EFFD12F8B4" box="[623,741,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Sphagnum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bogs, lakes, ponds, springs and seepages and even seasonally damp soil in shade (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FE9EF88BFDD5F898" author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[360,546,1886,1912]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" pagination="364 - 369" refId="ref33036" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2009) Nomenclatural notes on Callitriche (Callitrichaceae) in North America. Novon 19: 364 - 369. https: // doi. org / 10.3417 / 2008030" type="journal article" year="2009">Lansdown 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Known elevation range 
<quantity id="1822C293FF91FF82FCB7F88BFC26F899" box="[833,977,1886,1913]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" unit="m" value="2350.0" valueMax="4600.0" valueMin="100.0">100–4600 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BF857FC61F87D" blockId="16.[136,1452,914,2057]" box="[189,918,1922,1949]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BF857FE4EF87C" bold="true" box="[189,441,1922,1948]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
—Least Concern (LC) (
<bibRefCitation id="BB4B1287FF91FF82FD35F857FC7DF87D" author="Lansdown, R. V." box="[707,906,1922,1949]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" pagination="64268932" refId="ref33234" refString="Lansdown, R. V. (2016 a) Callitriche heterophylla. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2016: e. T 64268932 A 66889787. https: // doi. org / 10.2305 / IUCN. UK. 2016 - 1. RLTS. T 64268932 A 66889787. en" type="journal article" year="2016">Lansdown 2016a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF656F76FF91FF82FF4BF873FC31F7E8" blockId="16.[136,1452,914,2057]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FF4BF873FEFEF820" bold="true" box="[189,265,1958,1984]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Notes:</emphasis>
—No specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FE19F872FD69F820" authorityName="Pursh" authorityYear="1814" box="[495,670,1958,1985]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FE19F872FD69F820" box="[495,670,1958,1985]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been confirmed from the region. Given the frequent problems with mis-identification of unfamiliar 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FDC5F81FFCFDF804" box="[563,778,1994,2020]" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FDC5F81FFD5BF804" box="[563,684,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, even by specialists, it is important that the identity of the populations from 
<collectingCountry id="A7CD2FE6FF91FF82FEB9F83AFE12F7E8" box="[335,485,2030,2057]" name="New Zealand" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
identified as 
<taxonomicName id="18DA14F5FF91FF82FD8BF83AFCDDF7E8" authorityName="Pursh" authorityYear="1814" box="[637,810,2030,2057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="16" pageNumber="259" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophylla">
<emphasis id="EDAEB364FF91FF82FD8BF83AFCDDF7E8" box="[637,810,2030,2057]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="259">C. heterophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
